sensation","Improved renal concentrating ability","Increased total body water content","Enhanced sodium conservation"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWith ageing, there is an \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased vulnerability to dehydration\u003C/strong\u003E due to multiple factors:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDecreased total body water content due to reduced muscle mass\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced thirst sensation leading to decreased fluid intake\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImpaired renal concentrating ability\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced renin-angiotensin-aldosterone system activity\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnhanced thirst sensation\u003C/strong\u003E - Ageing reduces thirst sensation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImproved renal concentrating ability\u003C/strong\u003E - Ageing impairs the kidney\u0027s ability to concentrate urine\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased total body water content\u003C/strong\u003E - Total body water decreases with age due to loss of muscle mass\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnhanced sodium conservation\u003C/strong\u003E - Ageing reduces the ability to conserve sodium\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Total body water content decreases with age due to reduced muscle mass and increased adipose tissue.","Elderly individuals have reduced thirst sensation and impaired renal concentrating ability.","Age-related changes in fluid balance increase vulnerability to dehydration."],"references":["Li S, Xiao X, Zhang X. Hydration Status in Older Adults: Current Knowledge and Future Challenges. Nutrients. 2023 Jun 2;15(11)